selectedVerses.text: They know not, nor do they discern, for he has shut their eyes, so that they cannot see, and their hearts, so that they cannot understand.
You say, 'God stores up their iniquity for their children.' Let him pay it out to them, that they may know it.
"You have heard their taunts, O LORD, all their plots against me.
When Abraham's servant heard their words, he bowed himself to the earth before the LORD.
And they shall bear their punishment--the punishment of the prophet and the punishment of the inquirer shall be alike--
